						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in survey No. 136 near the image Vīrabhadra.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivadēva, 1559 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1481, Siddhārthin, Āshāḍha śu. 12, Friday</hi> corresponding to 1559 A.D. June 16.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records a gift of land in the village Gaṅgapērūru situated in the Siddhavaṭaṁ-sīma in the Udayagiri-rājya by Nāgarājayyadēva-Mahārāju on the orders of the king for the worship and offerings to the god Raghunāyakulu of Oṇṭimiṭṭa.</p>						

						</summary>
